cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the interpretation of deep features learned by convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for city recognition. The paper uses techniques such as Grad-CAM and semantic segmentation to interpret the deep representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses unsupervised clustering and statistical measures to evaluate the interpretability of discriminate objects, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the influence of network architectures and random initializations in training, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
